1. Install Nodejs and Npm 
* Install Npm: 
	-> apt-get install npm
 	-> sudo apt-get update
* Install Nodejs:
 	-> sudo n lastest 
	-> sudo n @version (Ex: sudo n 10. )
* Make an package.json file with npm: 
	-> npm init
2. Install Webpack
	-> npm install webpack --save-dev (*--save-dev: deveplopment tool)
3. Install Webpack command line interface:
	-> npm install webpack-cli --save-dev 
4. Install Webpack dev server (automatically reload the page when we save our code): 
	-> npm install webpack-dev-server --save-dev
5. Webpack html-plugin ???
	-> npm install html-webpack-plugin --save-dev
6. Install Babel
	-> npm install babel-preset-env babel-loader --save-dev
	-> npm install @babel/core --save
	-> Install Babel polyfill: npm install babel-polyfill --save (*--save: dependecy in code)
7. Install and run Sass
	-> "npm install node-sass --save-dev"
	(if not use this command: "npm install --save-dev node-sass --unsafe-perm=true --allow-root)"
	-> Compile to CSS: "node-sass input:path output:path"
